"Jang Ji Myung."

244
00:08:28,429 --> 00:08:31,198
"Abalone shell, gold dust, and even rocks."

245
00:08:31,199 --> 00:08:34,069
"Everything from nature becomes an ingredient for me."

246
00:08:34,129 --> 00:08:35,399
Are we meeting a crafter?

247
00:08:35,939 --> 00:08:38,709
"In my day-to-day life, I revive traces from hundreds of years ago."

248
00:08:38,909 --> 00:08:40,569
"Please leave the traces..."

249
00:08:40,639 --> 00:08:43,009
"of Whenever Possible in my studio in Ssangmun-dong."

250
00:08:43,109 --> 00:08:46,479
"P.S. Yeon Seok, Goo Dong Mae's fan is waiting for you."

251
00:08:47,449 --> 00:08:48,679
My fan is waiting for me.

252
00:08:49,249 --> 00:08:51,318
- Abalone shells and gold dust.
- Nacre?

253
00:08:51,319 --> 00:08:53,218
- It could be nacre.
- Right.

254
00:08:53,219 --> 00:08:55,049
- Right?
- They might be for handicrafts.

255
00:08:55,319 --> 00:08:57,058
- Let's go.
- We can just walk there.

256
00:08:57,059 --> 00:08:58,119
- It will only take nine minutes.
- Let's go.

257
00:08:58,519 --> 00:09:00,489
Yeon Seok, you really had no idea?

258
00:09:00,829 --> 00:09:02,298
- That we were coming?
- They didn't tell me.

259
00:09:02,299 --> 00:09:03,359
We didn't know.

260
00:09:03,829 --> 00:09:05,298
It's been ages since Hee Jun and I last met.

261
00:09:05,299 --> 00:09:06,469
Yes, that's right.

262
00:09:07,099 --> 00:09:08,569
The weather is great today.

263
00:09:08,839 --> 00:09:10,539
- It's spring.
- It's gotten much warmer.

264
00:09:10,669 --> 00:09:12,939
- Yes, it has. It's spring now.
- Seriously.

265
00:09:13,539 --> 00:09:16,079
- It's spring now.
- I love how sunny it is.

266
00:09:16,539 --> 00:09:19,348
Fine dust concentrations peak when the weather begins to warm up.

267
00:09:19,349 --> 00:09:20,849
- We can still see the mountain.
- Yes.

268
00:09:20,909 --> 00:09:22,219
Look over there. It's Insu Peak.

269
00:09:22,349 --> 00:09:24,049
- Insu Peak.
- Yes, Insu Peak.

270
00:09:24,679 --> 00:09:26,989
I can even see the peak of Mount Bukhan.

271
00:09:27,149 --> 00:09:28,858
- I can see everything from here.
- That's why...

272
00:09:28,859 --> 00:09:30,558
Insu Peak is mentioned in the school song...

273
00:09:30,559 --> 00:09:31,889
of the nearby schools.

274
00:09:32,459 --> 00:09:34,628
- The energy from the peak.
- Right. The energy...

275
00:09:34,629 --> 00:09:36,228
- is often mentioned in those songs.
- Right.

276
00:09:36,229 --> 00:09:37,299
Yes.

277
00:09:37,759 --> 00:09:39,528
- Hee Jun, you only have one kid?
- Yes?

278
00:09:39,529 --> 00:09:41,468
- Yes, he's 8.
- I see. He's 8.

279
00:09:41,469 --> 00:09:43,339
- He started elementary school.
- Yes, he did.

280
00:09:43,799 --> 00:09:46,638
- The first day of school...
- I got so emotional.

281
00:09:46,639 --> 00:09:47,809
- You got emotional, right?
- Yes.

282
00:09:48,569 --> 00:09:49,638
Parents tear up on the graduation day...

283
00:09:49,639 --> 00:09:51,339
- of kindergarten too.
- Yes, I did too.

284
00:09:51,679 --> 00:09:54,849
My son has lunch after fourth period.

285
00:09:54,949 --> 00:09:58,348
Then he has 30 minutes until his fifth period...

286
00:09:58,349 --> 00:10:00,389
- begins.
- Yes.

287
00:10:00,819 --> 00:10:04,388
I'm so worried about how he's going to find the classroom.

288
00:10:04,389 --> 00:10:05,729
- He has to go to the classroom?
- Yes.

289
00:10:05,959 --> 00:10:07,489
I asked him how he found the classroom.

290
00:10:07,759 --> 00:10:09,459
He said he was playing soccer in the school yard...

291
00:10:09,629 --> 00:10:10,898
and then went to class after checking the time...

292
00:10:10,899 --> 00:10:12,129
- on the big clock.
- He went to class?

293
00:10:12,829 --> 00:10:15,128
- I was so proud of him.
- Of course, you were.

294
00:10:15,129 --> 00:10:16,898
- Parents get proud and emotional...
- Right.

295
00:10:16,899 --> 00:10:18,739
- over every small thing.
- Right.

296
00:10:19,909 --> 00:10:22,538
- So your son is 5?
- He turned 6.

297
00:10:22,539 --> 00:10:23,778
- He turned 6?
- He's 6?

298
00:10:23,779 --> 00:10:27,179
Yes. He recently started kindergarten.

299
00:10:28,609 --> 00:10:31,019
- You must be proud of him.
- Yes, I was.

300
00:10:31,279 --> 00:10:33,319
Time really flies by.

301
00:10:33,749 --> 00:10:37,419
You know what? This is the perfect weather...

302
00:10:38,259 --> 00:10:39,888
for a walk.

303
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:41,458
- Filming a drama now...
- It's pretty good.

304
00:10:41,459 --> 00:10:43,129
- Starting now...
- Now is a good time, right?

305
00:10:43,229 --> 00:10:44,329
But...

306
00:10:44,559 --> 00:10:46,269
- Hello.
- Hello.

307
00:10:46,529 --> 00:10:48,729
- Hello.
- Hello.

308
00:10:48,999 --> 00:10:50,338
- Hello.
- Gosh, it's Yeon Seok.

309
00:10:50,339 --> 00:10:51,468
- Hello.
- My gosh.

310
00:10:51,469 --> 00:10:52,569
He's so handsome.

311
00:10:53,539 --> 00:10:54,639
Thank you.

312
00:10:55,039 --> 00:10:56,208
- "My gosh."
- But...

313
00:10:56,209 --> 00:10:59,149
"My gosh. Hey, Yeon Seok."

314
00:11:01,009 --> 00:11:02,579
I'm quite disappointed by them.

315
00:11:03,049 --> 00:11:04,649
They complimented only Yeon Seok's looks.

316
00:11:05,319 --> 00:11:07,419
- "Gosh, look who it is."
- There are four of us here.

317
00:11:07,489 --> 00:11:10,358
- "My goodness. You're so handsome."
- There are four of us here.

318
00:11:10,359 --> 00:11:11,688
They only complimented him.

319
00:11:11,689 --> 00:11:13,559
- So they don't lie.
- Right.

320
00:11:13,659 --> 00:11:15,188
Hee Jun, they don't lie.

321
00:11:15,189 --> 00:11:16,828
- There's nothing we can do.
- There's nothing we can do.

322
00:11:16,829 --> 00:11:19,298
They don't compliment our looks and say we look handsome...

323
00:11:19,299 --> 00:11:20,969
no matter how close we get.

324
00:11:22,769 --> 00:11:23,969
- They don't do that.
- Right?

325
00:11:24,139 --> 00:11:25,338
But you don't give out...

326
00:11:25,339 --> 00:11:27,309
- empty compliments either.
- I don't give empty compliments.

327
00:11:27,639 --> 00:11:29,009
But sometimes, I just blurt it out.

328
00:11:29,309 --> 00:11:30,839
- You just blurt it out?
- "He's so handsome."

329
00:11:31,039 --> 00:11:32,978
- Or... "He's so cool."
- Some guys are just that handsome.

330
00:11:32,979 --> 00:11:34,148
- Right.
- Yes.

331
00:11:34,149 --> 00:11:35,849
- I can't help it.
- Right.

332
00:11:36,179 --> 00:11:38,578
- Jinyoung.
- Oh, right.

333
00:11:38,579 --> 00:11:40,648
- Who?
- Jinyoung of GOT7.

334
00:11:40,649 --> 00:11:43,488
- Jinyoung of GOT7.
- I met him recently.

335
00:11:43,489 --> 00:11:45,288
- I was talking to him.
- He has beautiful eyes.

336
00:11:45,289 --> 00:11:46,929
- Right.
- While talking to him, I said,

337
00:11:47,189 --> 00:11:49,359
"You have the prettiest eyes."

338
00:11:49,459 --> 00:11:51,359
- I just blurted it out. You know?
- Yes.

339
00:11:51,599 --> 00:11:53,869
Jinyoung reminded me of myself.

340
00:11:54,099 --> 00:11:56,098
- Come on.
- Growing up in Gyeongsang...

341
00:11:56,099 --> 00:11:58,298
What? I didn't say we looked alike.

342
00:11:58,299 --> 00:12:00,138
- But that's what you were implying.
- No, growing up...

343
00:12:00,139 --> 00:12:01,139
It's Ko Gil Dong.

344
00:12:01,140 --> 00:12:03,708
- It's the hometown of Dooly.
- That's right.

345
00:12:03,709 --> 00:12:05,409
- It's Dooly's hometown.
- Ssangmun-dong?

346
00:12:05,579 --> 00:12:06,748
- Ssangmun-dong and Ko Gil Dong.
- We both grew up...

347
00:12:06,749 --> 00:12:07,908
in Gyeongsang Province,

348
00:12:07,909 --> 00:12:08,948
and transferred to a school...

349
00:12:08,949 --> 00:12:10,019
- in Seoul.
- Ssangmun-dong is Dooly's hometown.

350
00:12:10,149 --> 00:12:13,689
The artist drew the cartoon here in Ssangmun-dong.

351
00:12:14,389 --> 00:12:15,859
(Disappointed)

352
00:12:16,459 --> 00:12:18,259
- We should...
- Where... Hold on.

353
00:12:18,719 --> 00:12:19,789
Where is it?

354
00:12:19,929 --> 00:12:21,858
I think it's on the second floor of that building.

355
00:12:21,859 --> 00:12:23,998
Is it the traditional art class? No?

356
00:12:23,999 --> 00:12:25,628
- That's it. Jang Ji Myung.
- "Traditional art..."

357
00:12:25,629 --> 00:12:27,068
- Jang Ji Myung.
- The name of the Whenever Guest...

358
00:12:27,069 --> 00:12:28,499
is written on the sign.

359
00:12:29,269 --> 00:12:30,769
If we're going to an art class...

360
00:12:31,339 --> 00:12:32,368
(Chuckling)

361
00:12:32,369 --> 00:12:35,038
- Well...
- Is one of you good at art?

362
00:12:35,039 --> 00:12:37,379
- Hee Jun is...
- He and I worked on some drawings.

363
00:12:37,579 --> 00:12:39,678
- Okay.
- We submitted our art to Kiaf.

364
00:12:39,679 --> 00:12:41,849
- Really?
- You showcased your art at Kiaf?

365
00:12:42,009 --> 00:12:44,718
- I just dabbled a bit next to him.
- Your guys were accepted into Kiaf?

366
00:12:44,719 --> 00:12:47,288
Hee Jun and his artist friend worked on a lot of paintings.

367
00:12:47,289 --> 00:12:48,389
Really?

368
00:12:48,489 --> 00:12:51,489
(The artwork Hee Jun and Hae Soo submitted together)

369
00:12:52,189 --> 00:12:53,928
(Then Hee Jun held a solo exhibit...)

370
00:12:53,929 --> 00:12:55,729
(and is running an art account on social media.)

371
00:12:55,999 --> 00:12:57,658
(An artist with a unique style)

372
00:12:57,659 --> 00:12:59,598
(Title: "Lifting")

373
00:12:59,599 --> 00:13:01,029
(Title: "Mask")

374
00:13:01,499 --> 00:13:03,168
- Really?
- I didn't know you were an artist.

375
00:13:03,169 --> 00:13:04,939
- He's a great artist.
- It's just a hobby.

376
00:13:05,499 --> 00:13:07,609
- A hobby?
- I'm curious about traditional art.

377
00:13:07,739 --> 00:13:09,909
- Let's go in. My gosh. He's...
- Shall we?

378
00:13:10,179 --> 00:13:12,549
I didn't know he was an artist.

379
00:13:13,109 --> 00:13:15,048
When I look at her name, this comes to my mind.

380
00:13:15,049 --> 00:13:16,648
The famous chant, "Jwauji jangjijiji."

381
00:13:16,649 --> 00:13:18,179
Why did you bring that up?

382
00:13:18,379 --> 00:13:20,389
- Because of her name?
- I...

383
00:13:21,589 --> 00:13:22,689
- Come on, Jae Seok.
- You know?

384
00:13:23,419 --> 00:13:24,688
You guys all know the chant.

385
00:13:24,689 --> 00:13:25,789
- Of course.
- We know it very well.

386
00:13:25,889 --> 00:13:26,958
How do I know it?

387
00:13:26,959 --> 00:13:29,858
- Jwauji jangjijiji - Jwauji jangjijiji

388
00:13:29,859 --> 00:13:30,959
- My gosh.
- It's...

389
00:13:31,159 --> 00:13:32,528
- What was that?
- Wasn't there choreography?

390
00:13:32,529 --> 00:13:34,498
Of course, it includes choreography too.

391
00:13:34,499 --> 00:13:36,739
- How did it go?
- I forgot.

392
00:13:36,969 --> 00:13:38,298
- Jwauji jangjijiji...
- I knew it when I was a kid.

393
00:13:38,299 --> 00:13:40,668
(They enter with a sense of nostalgia.)

394
00:13:40,669 --> 00:13:42,638
- Do we have to take off our shoes?
- We have to take off our shoes.

395
00:13:42,639 --> 00:13:43,678
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

396
00:13:43,679 --> 00:13:44,779
- Yes?
- Is anyone here?

397
00:13:45,009 --> 00:13:46,309
Yes, come on in.

398
00:13:46,679 --> 00:13:47,779
Can we enter?

399
00:13:48,049 --> 00:13:49,049
(Screaming)

400
00:13:50,249 --> 00:13:51,849
- My gosh. No way.
- Hello.

401
00:13:52,649 --> 00:13:53,889
- She went for it.
- Hello.

402
00:13:54,219 --> 00:13:55,819
- Hello. Nice to meet you.
- Ji Myung.

403
00:13:56,159 --> 00:13:58,259
My gosh. I won't be able to move then.

404
00:13:58,659 --> 00:13:59,929
Don't say hello to me.

405
00:14:00,989 --> 00:14:02,028
Goo Dong Mae is here.

406
00:14:02,029 --> 00:14:03,499
What a cozy place.

407
00:14:04,129 --> 00:14:05,969
- It's nice here, isn't it?
- This place...

408
00:14:06,199 --> 00:14:08,668
- Ji Myung? Hello.
- Gosh.

409
00:14:08,669 --> 00:14:11,338
- You're Jwauji Jangjijiji, right?
- Jwauji jangjijiji.

410
00:14:11,339 --> 00:14:12,608
- That was it?
- Hello.

411
00:14:12,609 --> 00:14:14,708
- My gosh. No way.
- Hello.

412
00:14:14,709 --> 00:14:16,479
- Park Hae Soo. Lee Hee Jun.
- "A Killer Paradox."

413
00:14:17,179 --> 00:14:18,679
- She gave us a big welcome.
- I see.

414
00:14:19,349 --> 00:14:20,949
So you work on Buddhist paintings.

415
00:14:21,349 --> 00:14:23,048
- How did you know?
- It's right there.

416
00:14:23,049 --> 00:14:25,479
- So you know about them.
- Of course.

417
00:14:26,049 --> 00:14:27,648
I do traditional art here.

418
00:14:27,649 --> 00:14:29,989
- I create traditional Korean art.
- Really?

419
00:14:30,819 --> 00:14:32,528
(The Whenever Guest, Jang Ji Myung...)

420
00:14:32,529 --> 00:14:34,628
Many of them are designated as cultural assets.

421
00:14:34,629 --> 00:14:36,629
And I work to promote our cultural heritage and art...

422
00:14:37,099 --> 00:14:39,998
- to more people.
- I see.

423
00:14:39,999 --> 00:14:41,769
(A mega-sized Buddhist painting, as tall as a 2 or 3-story building)

424
00:14:42,439 --> 00:14:43,898
(She participated in restoring the replica...)

425
00:14:43,899 --> 00:14:45,338
(of "Hanging Painting of Hwaeom Temple.")

426
00:14:45,339 --> 00:14:46,369
(The Whenever Guest)

427
00:14:46,769 --> 00:14:48,709
(The restored signboard at Woljeong Temple)

428
00:14:49,639 --> 00:14:52,609
(She worked on numerous Buddhist paintings from palaces and temples.)

429
00:14:53,409 --> 00:14:54,648
(An artist who specializes in preserving our national heritage)

430
00:14:54,649 --> 00:14:56,279
- She must be so detailed.
- Of course.

431
00:14:56,919 --> 00:14:58,179
This is so cool.

432
00:14:58,519 --> 00:15:01,888
So she specializes in restoring and preserving...

433
00:15:01,889 --> 00:15:04,158
- our national paintings.
- I help preserve them too.

434
00:15:04,159 --> 00:15:05,358
- Right.
- That's what you do.

435
00:15:05,359 --> 00:15:06,559
We must restore and preserve our art.

436
00:15:06,759 --> 00:15:10,059
- Time will continue to pass.
- Right.

437
00:15:10,259 --> 00:15:11,499
My gosh, don't look at me.

438
00:15:12,999 --> 00:15:14,168
- Pardon?
- I'm nervous.

439
00:15:14,169 --> 00:15:15,428
- My mind is going blank.
- I see.

440
00:15:15,429 --> 00:15:16,898
So you're Goo Dong Mae's fan.

441
00:15:16,899 --> 00:15:17,899
(She can't meet his gaze.)

442
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:19,509
Why are you looking at me when you talk?

443
00:15:20,009 --> 00:15:21,208
- I noticed that...
- The two of us...

444
00:15:21,209 --> 00:15:23,409
- she had no problem looking at us.
- Do you feel comfortable around me?

445
00:15:23,479 --> 00:15:25,849
Ssangmun-dong is hurting my feelings.

446
00:15:26,049 --> 00:15:27,278
- It was like...
- Hee Jun.

447
00:15:27,279 --> 00:15:28,578
- we were taking her class.
- Hae Soo.

448
00:15:28,579 --> 00:15:30,318
Remember when we were walking on the street?

449
00:15:30,319 --> 00:15:31,378
- Gosh, no.
- The same thing happened just now.

450
00:15:31,379 --> 00:15:33,188
- This is my hometown. Come on.
- It's nothing like that.

451
00:15:33,189 --> 00:15:35,588
You can't look that way because Goo Dong Mae is there.

452
00:15:35,589 --> 00:15:37,019
She looked at Hee Jun the most.

453
00:15:37,319 --> 00:15:38,588
(Feeling the most comfortable around him)

454
00:15:38,589 --> 00:15:39,828
- I was next.
- And then me.

455
00:15:39,829 --> 00:15:41,029
- Then it was Hae Soo.
- Yes.

456
00:15:41,289 --> 00:15:42,498
(Trying to focus)

457
00:15:42,499 --> 00:15:45,729
What about those portraits?

458
00:15:45,869 --> 00:15:46,928
Yes?

459
00:15:46,929 --> 00:15:48,768
- That's Yi Hwang's portrait.
- Right.

460
00:15:48,769 --> 00:15:50,339
Is that considered a folk painting?

461
00:15:50,439 --> 00:15:53,609
Folk painting? Well, it's a replica.

462
00:15:53,939 --> 00:15:56,808
I heard these two were good at work too.

463
00:15:56,809 --> 00:15:58,479
- Really?
- We draw as a hobby.

464
00:15:58,609 --> 00:16:01,049
- I see.
- They showcased their art at Kiaf.

465
00:16:02,379 --> 00:16:03,918
Right. Artists...

466
00:16:03,919 --> 00:16:05,549
You must feel very comfortable around Hee Jun.

467
00:16:05,679 --> 00:16:06,688
She seemed super relaxed.

468
00:16:06,689 --> 00:16:08,649
He's wearing yellow.

469
00:16:09,389 --> 00:16:11,459
- That's why, right?
- He's wearing yellow.

470
00:16:13,359 --> 00:16:14,659
But you did this with your shoulders.

471
00:16:16,299 --> 00:16:17,428
She has her back to him.

472
00:16:17,429 --> 00:16:19,098
(She faces away from her favorite actor.)

473
00:16:19,099 --> 00:16:21,228
She didn't have to turn her back to me.

474
00:16:21,229 --> 00:16:22,499
Come on.

475
00:16:23,439 --> 00:16:24,699
(Shy)

476
00:16:24,799 --> 00:16:28,739
How long have you been running this place?

477
00:16:28,809 --> 00:16:31,538
I opened my studio right after giving birth.

478
00:16:31,539 --> 00:16:33,378
But I'm from Ssangmun-dong.

479
00:16:33,379 --> 00:16:36,018
- Really?
- I went to a nearby high school.

480
00:16:36,019 --> 00:16:37,418
Which one? The all-girls high school?

481
00:16:37,419 --> 00:16:38,778
Singyeong Girls' High School.

482
00:16:38,779 --> 00:16:41,948
- Kim Han Seok's older brother...
- Yes.

483
00:16:41,949 --> 00:16:43,459
- He was a teacher.
- But why do you keep doing this?

484
00:16:43,719 --> 00:16:46,188
Han Seok used to make this gesture.

485
00:16:46,189 --> 00:16:47,189
(An outdated gesture)

486
00:16:47,190 --> 00:16:48,729
It feels like we've gone back in time.

487
00:16:49,259 --> 00:16:50,559
(Loving it)

488
00:16:50,759 --> 00:16:51,759
(Shooting)

489
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:52,828
(Playing along)

490
00:16:52,829 --> 00:16:55,268
(The mid-lifers are taking a walk down memory lane.)

491
00:16:55,269 --> 00:16:57,039
- So everyone knows that.
- Yes.

492
00:16:57,339 --> 00:16:58,699
It's a huge relief, by the way.

493
00:16:59,099 --> 00:17:00,938
We saw your name when we were coming up.

494
00:17:00,939 --> 00:17:02,938
- Yes.
- We saw your name, Jang Ji Myung.

495
00:17:02,939 --> 00:17:04,879
We talked about the famous chant, jwauji jangjijiji.

496
00:17:05,109 --> 00:17:07,749
She happened to know exactly what we were talking about.

497
00:17:07,909 --> 00:17:10,548
We forgot the dance move that went with it, but you showed us.

498
00:17:10,549 --> 00:17:13,718
- I'm also a mid-lifer.
- Did your friends call you that...

499
00:17:13,719 --> 00:17:15,318
as a nickname when you were a kid?

500
00:17:15,319 --> 00:17:17,889
- Jwauji jangjijiji? Yes, they did.
- They did?

501
00:17:18,959 --> 00:17:20,888
Playful friends always tease people about their name.

502
00:17:20,889 --> 00:17:22,288
- There's always a friend like me.
- Right.

503
00:17:22,289 --> 00:17:24,559
Yes, I had a friend like you. His name was Kim Nam Hyun.

504
00:17:25,259 --> 00:17:26,898
- Hello.
- Whenever he saw me, he said,

505
00:17:26,899 --> 00:17:28,998
"Jwauji jangjijiji." He used to say that all the time.

506
00:17:28,999 --> 00:17:29,999
(He said the chant whenever he met her.)

507
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,438
So you had a friend like me.

508
00:17:31,439 --> 00:17:34,768
Hold on. Shouldn't you have lunch around this time of the day?

509
00:17:34,769 --> 00:17:37,478
Right. I either have lunch...

510
00:17:37,479 --> 00:17:38,978
or review the materials for my meetings.

511
00:17:38,979 --> 00:17:40,478
Sometimes, I read books.

512
00:17:40,479 --> 00:17:41,879
What do you usually eat for lunch?

513
00:17:42,179 --> 00:17:43,548
I eat cup noodles.

514
00:17:43,549 --> 00:17:44,919
- My gosh.
- Cup noodles.

515
00:17:45,279 --> 00:17:47,388
- So ramyeon?
- I'd love to have a grand meal.

516
00:17:47,389 --> 00:17:48,548
- But...
- What do you like to eat then?

517
00:17:48,549 --> 00:17:49,819
- I like sushi.
- Sushi?

518
00:17:50,189 --> 00:17:52,158
- Sushi.
- You're indeed Dong Mae's fan.

519
00:17:52,159 --> 00:17:53,828
(She's indeed Dong Mae's fan.)

520
00:17:53,829 --> 00:17:57,028
- I also like sushi. Yes.
- My daughter...

521
00:17:57,029 --> 00:17:58,829
- thinks you're Japanese.
- Oh, me?

522
00:17:59,299 --> 00:18:01,429
- I...
- I see.

523
00:18:01,569 --> 00:18:04,068
I used Japanese in the drama.

524
00:18:04,069 --> 00:18:06,368
- Right. Your outfit and everything.
- The outfit. Yes.

525
00:18:06,369 --> 00:18:08,808
I rewatch your drama all the time. My students ask me,

526
00:18:08,809 --> 00:18:11,578
"I'm sorry, but can you stop watching the drama?"

527
00:18:11,579 --> 00:18:13,378
- They'd say that?
- How many times did you watch it?

528
00:18:13,379 --> 00:18:15,249
- About 100 times.
- What?

529
00:18:15,579 --> 00:18:16,878
I've memorized some of the lines.

530
00:18:16,879 --> 00:18:18,719
- Which one?
- Why don't you say the lines?

531
00:18:18,949 --> 00:18:20,748
- I'm too nervous to do it.
- Which one?

532
00:18:20,749 --> 00:18:24,658
I'll tell you about the most memorable scene.

533
00:18:24,659 --> 00:18:26,558
You were holding...

534
00:18:26,559 --> 00:18:28,859
- the hem of her skirt.
- When I held the hem of her skirt.

535
00:18:29,359 --> 00:18:30,598
(Thinking about the scene makes her heart race.)

536
00:18:30,599 --> 00:18:32,529
She finally looked him in the eye.

537
00:18:33,499 --> 00:18:35,999
- I held the hem of her skirt.
- Yes.

538
00:18:36,699 --> 00:18:38,069
Can you hold my hand?

539
00:18:38,469 --> 00:18:39,609
My lady...

540
00:18:39,669 --> 00:18:40,669
(Exclaiming)

541
00:18:40,969 --> 00:18:43,809
What are you doing? What was that?

542
00:18:43,839 --> 00:18:45,508
- That was...
- Wait.

543
00:18:45,509 --> 00:18:46,649
What was that all about?

544
00:18:46,849 --> 00:18:49,349
- What was that?
- Was that necessary?

545
00:18:49,749 --> 00:18:50,849
What are you doing?

546
00:18:51,449 --> 00:18:52,989
- What was that?
- I'm sorry.

547
00:18:53,749 --> 00:18:56,488
- It's one of the famous scenes...
- My gosh. The scene...

548
00:18:56,489 --> 00:18:57,888
- in "Mr. Sunshine."
- Of course, I know.

549
00:18:57,889 --> 00:18:59,928
- I'm hooked on the drama.
- I know the scene.

550
00:18:59,929 --> 00:19:01,958
Did you like any drama or movie that they starred in?

551
00:19:01,959 --> 00:19:04,328
I really liked "A Killer Paradox."

552
00:19:04,329 --> 00:19:07,068
In your drama, North Korea and South Korea...

553
00:19:07,069 --> 00:19:09,869
- You mean "Money Heist?"
- "Money Heist."

554
00:19:09,969 --> 00:19:11,298
- I really liked it.
- I played a North Korean.

555
00:19:11,299 --> 00:19:12,969
Both of you were so charismatic.

556
00:19:13,739 --> 00:19:15,169
Let me try it too.

557
00:19:15,339 --> 00:19:17,679
(Hee Dong Mae doesn't hold back.)

558
00:19:18,639 --> 00:19:19,808
(The original actor is satisfied.)

559
00:19:19,809 --> 00:19:20,809
Great job.

560
00:19:21,149 --> 00:19:22,149
That was good.

561
00:19:22,150 --> 00:19:23,178
(They brush their nose to compliment his wit.)

562
00:19:23,179 --> 00:19:24,479
That was good, Hee Jun.

563
00:19:24,619 --> 00:19:25,648
You're growing on us.

564
00:19:25,649 --> 00:19:26,649
(His wit is growing on us.)

565
00:19:26,650 --> 00:19:27,689
Okay.

566
00:19:27,989 --> 00:19:30,588
- By the way, I love her studio.
- Right.

567
00:19:30,589 --> 00:19:32,559
- Should I say it's cozy?
- It's cozy.

568
00:19:33,129 --> 00:19:34,359
(Turning around)

569
00:19:34,659 --> 00:19:36,298
It must be because she has many paintings with good energy.

570
00:19:36,299 --> 00:19:37,299
- Right.
- I feel relaxed here.

571
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:38,559
Over there. That one.

572
00:19:38,799 --> 00:19:40,099
- I'd love to learn more about it.
- Oh, that one?

573
00:19:40,569 --> 00:19:44,238
- It was displayed in Italy.
- Gosh, that painting...

574
00:19:44,239 --> 00:19:45,568
I couldn't stop looking at it.

575
00:19:45,569 --> 00:19:47,268
- Did you paint it yourself?
- You can see it up close.

576
00:19:47,269 --> 00:19:48,968
- Really?
- You used gold, right?

577
00:19:48,969 --> 00:19:50,338
- Right. I used pure gold.
- Gold.

578
00:19:50,339 --> 00:19:51,509
- Pure gold?
- Yes.

579
00:19:53,009 --> 00:19:55,578
(From the background to the various accessories,)

580
00:19:55,579 --> 00:19:56,749
This is impressive.

581
00:19:57,379 --> 00:19:59,118
(the painting is delicately crafted in pure gold.)

582
00:19:59,119 --> 00:20:02,718
If you look over here, this part...

583
00:20:02,719 --> 00:20:04,289
- That's nacre.
- It's nacre.

584
00:20:04,589 --> 00:20:06,959
- I see.
- It's processed nacre.

585
00:20:07,259 --> 00:20:09,699
Clam shells were processed, so they could be used in my artwork.

586
00:20:09,859 --> 00:20:11,399
I put nacre on my painting.

587
00:20:11,429 --> 00:20:14,728
This part has thicker pieces of nacre.

588
00:20:14,729 --> 00:20:18,238
- That's right.
- I see smaller pieces here.

589
00:20:18,239 --> 00:20:20,009
My gosh. They're all pieces of nacre?

590
00:20:20,239 --> 00:20:23,108
As for the paints used in my artwork,

591
00:20:23,109 --> 00:20:25,208
they aren't your typical paints.

592
00:20:25,209 --> 00:20:27,409
- They're not ordinary paints.
- Right.

593
00:20:27,879 --> 00:20:29,178
- They're natural paints...
- I see. They are...

594
00:20:29,179 --> 00:20:30,848
- natural paints.
- made from rocks and oyster shells.

595
00:20:30,849 --> 00:20:32,478
Like the food we eat.

596
00:20:32,479 --> 00:20:34,288
- From natural ingredients.
- That's amazing.

597
00:20:34,289 --> 00:20:36,688
Her painting doesn't look like a regular painting.

598
00:20:36,689 --> 00:20:37,689
How should I put it?

599
00:20:37,690 --> 00:20:39,428
It has a three-dimensional vibe...

600
00:20:39,429 --> 00:20:41,158
- as if it's alive.
- Right?

601
00:20:41,159 --> 00:20:42,998
How long did it take to finish this?

602
00:20:42,999 --> 00:20:44,998
It took a year for me to finish this.

603
00:20:44,999 --> 00:20:47,099
- Right. This is...
- It took a year.

604
00:20:47,269 --> 00:20:49,898
You'll need more than a few months to complete a piece like this.

605
00:20:49,899 --> 00:20:51,699
- This is impressive.
- It looks three-dimensional.

606
00:20:51,839 --> 00:20:54,338
- Thank you.
- I mean it. This is incredible.

607
00:20:54,339 --> 00:20:56,279
Okay. All right. We need to...

608
00:20:56,609 --> 00:20:58,138
- do a good job today.
- Yes.

609
00:20:58,139 --> 00:21:00,149
- We must do well.
- We ought to boost...

610
00:21:00,479 --> 00:21:02,848
her energy during her spare time.

611
00:21:02,849 --> 00:21:04,278
Hee Jun, you can roll it first.

612
00:21:04,279 --> 00:21:06,149
- Up to two.
- Great. Throw it gently here.

613
00:21:08,719 --> 00:21:09,719
Behind you.

614
00:21:10,089 --> 00:21:11,159
- Where did it go?
- Let's see.

615
00:21:11,389 --> 00:21:13,728
- Two.
- Oh, my.

616
00:21:13,729 --> 00:21:15,659
- Nice.
- Two? Really?

617
00:21:15,829 --> 00:21:16,929
We're off to a great start.

618
00:21:17,459 --> 00:21:18,598
I'm feeling good today.

619
00:21:18,599 --> 00:21:20,228
- My gosh.
- All right.

620
00:21:20,229 --> 00:21:21,728
- This studio has nice energy.
- The present.

621
00:21:21,729 --> 00:21:22,839
I totally agree.

622
00:21:22,869 --> 00:21:24,599
- Let's find out what the prize is.
- The prize.

623
00:21:25,599 --> 00:21:29,038
"I travel all over Korea to restore our national paintings."

624
00:21:29,039 --> 00:21:31,078
"An essential item to block out the UV light."

625
00:21:31,079 --> 00:21:33,609
"A linen bucket hat from H Brand."

626
00:21:34,179 --> 00:21:35,249
What's that?

627
00:21:35,909 --> 00:21:37,318
- That looks fancy.
- My gosh.

628
00:21:37,319 --> 00:21:39,278
I thought it'd be sunscreen to block out the UV light.

629
00:21:39,279 --> 00:21:40,519
Same here. It thought so too.

630
00:21:40,989 --> 00:21:43,619
- I don't have it.
- How beautiful.

631
00:21:43,859 --> 00:21:46,559
- It's a hat an artist would wear.
- How luxurious.

632
00:21:46,889 --> 00:21:48,429
When you were in Italy...

633
00:21:48,929 --> 00:21:51,199
We'll play a game with Hae Soo and Hee Jun now.

634
00:21:51,599 --> 00:21:52,969
Please complete Round One.

635
00:21:53,099 --> 00:21:54,498
(A bucket hat is at stake on this mission.)

636
00:21:54,499 --> 00:21:56,499
(Fly, Brush!)

637
00:21:56,539 --> 00:21:57,968
(Slap the brush on top of an upside-down bucket.)

638
00:21:57,969 --> 00:21:59,968
(2 brushes must land inside the box.)

639
00:21:59,969 --> 00:22:03,539
(They're given 10 brushes and 30 seconds to finish.)

640
00:22:03,639 --> 00:22:05,578
- I see. Just like this?
- We have to slap it?

641
00:22:05,579 --> 00:22:06,579
Like the game, tipcat?

642
00:22:06,909 --> 00:22:09,148
- We need to make it bounce up.
- Seriously.

643
00:22:09,149 --> 00:22:10,149
(Place it on the bucket and make it land in the box.)

644
00:22:10,150 --> 00:22:11,949
- I hit it too hard.
- Just like that?

645
00:22:12,779 --> 00:22:14,688
- This isn't easy.
- It must travel...

646
00:22:14,689 --> 00:22:16,048
- quite far.
- It needs to travel quite far.

647
00:22:16,049 --> 00:22:17,119
Or we can try this.

648
00:22:18,789 --> 00:22:20,088
It's too far.

649
00:22:20,089 --> 00:22:22,429
Gosh, they keep coming up with all kinds of games.

650
00:22:22,489 --> 00:22:23,798
- Hee Jun.
- Hee Jun.

651
00:22:23,799 --> 00:22:26,269
Hee Jun probably held a lot of brushes for his art.

652
00:22:26,369 --> 00:22:27,929
It's not easy to place it on the bucket.

653
00:22:27,969 --> 00:22:29,429
- It's not working.
- Because it moves.

654
00:22:30,839 --> 00:22:32,598
- My gosh. All right.
- Hee Jun.

655
00:22:32,599 --> 00:22:33,608
You hit too hard.

656
00:22:33,609 --> 00:22:35,139
- He was doing archery.
- The brush...

657
00:22:36,109 --> 00:22:37,109
(Approaching)

658
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:38,508
Don't worry. We can do this.

659
00:22:38,509 --> 00:22:39,549
You got this.

660
00:22:40,109 --> 00:22:41,148
You hit too hard.

661
00:22:41,149 --> 00:22:43,219
- You try it. Yes.
- Should I try it?

662
00:22:43,419 --> 00:22:44,849
It's so hard.

663
00:22:46,849 --> 00:22:48,148
- Gosh.
- Oh, my. Nice.

664
00:22:48,149 --> 00:22:49,219
- Try it again.
- You got close.

665
00:22:50,319 --> 00:22:52,559
(Carefully setting it up)

666
00:22:57,959 --> 00:22:59,099
- I got it.
- No way.

667
00:22:59,529 --> 00:23:00,529
- Okay.
- Yes.

668
00:23:00,769 --> 00:23:01,798
Great.

669
00:23:01,799 --> 00:23:02,938
(I think they can pull it off.)

670
00:23:02,939 --> 00:23:04,168
- Should we go for it?
- My gosh.

671
00:23:04,169 --> 00:23:05,398
- Let's try for Round One.
- All right.

672
00:23:05,399 --> 00:23:06,608
- Let's do a group cheer.
- Bring it in.

673
00:23:06,609 --> 00:23:07,938
- All right.
- You too.

674
00:23:07,939 --> 00:23:09,468
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

675
00:23:09,469 --> 00:23:10,578
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

676
00:23:10,579 --> 00:23:11,579
(Out of 10 total tries, they're on try number 1.)

677
00:23:11,580 --> 00:23:13,208
- We'll do 2. And they'll do 3.
- Yes.

678
00:23:13,209 --> 00:23:14,979
- Two, two, three, and three.
- Yes.

679
00:23:15,309 --> 00:23:16,419
All right. I'll go first.

680
00:23:16,519 --> 00:23:17,778
I shouldn't hit all of them at once.

681
00:23:17,779 --> 00:23:21,148
(Out of 10 total tries, they're on try number 1.)

682
00:23:21,149 --> 00:23:22,149
Set.

683
00:23:23,659 --> 00:23:24,989
- Gosh.
- Jae Seok.

684
00:23:25,459 --> 00:23:26,829
It gets hard when he goes on an actual game.

685
00:23:26,959 --> 00:23:28,228
- When he goes on an actual game...
- Gosh.

686
00:23:28,229 --> 00:23:30,199
Jae Seok, why did you hit it so hard?

687
00:23:30,659 --> 00:23:32,559
- Why did it fly so far?
- Loosen up.

688
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:34,969
- Stay calm.
- This much...

689
00:23:36,799 --> 00:23:38,139
- This much...
- Nice.

690
00:23:38,799 --> 00:23:40,269
- He's good.
- That was good.

691
00:23:40,369 --> 00:23:41,468
Right here.

692
00:23:41,469 --> 00:23:43,309
(Yeon Seok's second brush)

693
00:23:44,439 --> 00:23:46,548
- I hit it too hard.
- You have ten seconds left.

694
00:23:46,549 --> 00:23:48,078
- We're running out of time.
- Hae Soo.

695
00:23:48,079 --> 00:23:50,778
(Hee Jun and Hae Soo have 3 brushes each.)

696
00:23:50,779 --> 00:23:52,218
- Hae Soo.
- Three.

697
00:23:52,219 --> 00:23:53,319
You're running out of time.

698
00:23:53,989 --> 00:23:55,489
- We have ten seconds left.
- Hey.

699
00:23:56,459 --> 00:23:57,459
(A perfect shot)

700
00:23:57,819 --> 00:24:01,289
(Just get one more brush in the box!)

701
00:24:01,459 --> 00:24:03,159
Four, three...

702
00:24:04,559 --> 00:24:06,598
- One.
- No!

703
00:24:06,599 --> 00:24:09,169
(They fail as they run out of time.)

704
00:24:09,369 --> 00:24:10,698
Hee Jun didn't even get to try.

705
00:24:10,699 --> 00:24:12,138
He didn't even get a chance. Thirty seconds is too short.

706
00:24:12,139 --> 00:24:13,208
It's okay.

707
00:24:13,209 --> 00:24:14,468
- The setup takes too long.
- I would probably have failed.

708
00:24:14,469 --> 00:24:16,608
- I don't think I can do it.
- I'm sorry, Hee Jun.

709
00:24:16,609 --> 00:24:17,609
It's okay.

710
00:24:17,610 --> 00:24:18,809
I was relieved, actually.

711
00:24:19,509 --> 00:24:21,578
- Hee Jun didn't get a chance.
- The setup takes time.

712
00:24:21,579 --> 00:24:23,248
It's taking longer than I expected.

713
00:24:23,249 --> 00:24:24,449
Setting it up...

714
00:24:26,289 --> 00:24:30,189
(It took a long time to set up the brush.)

715
00:24:31,289 --> 00:24:33,189
We need to pick up the pace.

716
00:24:33,929 --> 00:24:35,989
- Around the edge of the red line.
- Really? It's around there.

717
00:24:36,359 --> 00:24:37,659
- It was too long.
- Yes. A bit.

718
00:24:38,799 --> 00:24:40,969
- Use less of the trapezius muscles.
- Gently.

719
00:24:42,469 --> 00:24:44,299
- So... Yes.
- He's engaging them too much.

720
00:24:44,439 --> 00:24:45,498
Don't use trapezius muscles.

721
00:24:45,499 --> 00:24:46,569
- Only use the triceps.
- Only the triceps.

722
00:24:47,609 --> 00:24:48,609
Darn it.

723
00:24:49,569 --> 00:24:50,839
Last one. Let me try one more.

724
00:24:51,379 --> 00:24:52,379
Don't hit it so hard.

725
00:24:52,380 --> 00:24:53,679
Is it okay to lose your temper here?

726
00:24:54,309 --> 00:24:56,279
We just need to get two brushes in the box.

727
00:24:58,579 --> 00:25:00,018
- Nice.
- Okay.

728
00:25:00,019 --> 00:25:02,588
- Let's do it, Hee Jun.
- Gosh, Hee Jun.

729
00:25:02,589 --> 00:25:03,788
- Go for it, Hee Jun.
