- Yes.

1226
00:42:15,827 --> 00:42:17,266
I didn't have much experience in variety shows,

1227
00:42:17,267 --> 00:42:20,567
so I thought I should be myself and enjoy it.

1228
00:42:21,037 --> 00:42:24,777
But I enjoyed it like a kid.

1229
00:42:25,377 --> 00:42:26,636
I danced and such.

1230
00:42:26,637 --> 00:42:28,476
I was wearing a sauna suit...

1231
00:42:28,477 --> 00:42:29,546
- Right.
- Yes.

1232
00:42:29,547 --> 00:42:31,776
and was all sweaty. But without thinking...

1233
00:42:31,777 --> 00:42:33,217
(Danced like crazy)

1234
00:42:34,077 --> 00:42:36,786
(31-year-old Hee Jun...)

1235
00:42:36,787 --> 00:42:38,757
(was particularly enthusiastic.)

1236
00:42:38,817 --> 00:42:40,457
(Nice!)

1237
00:42:40,917 --> 00:42:42,226
His purity is good, no?

1238
00:42:42,227 --> 00:42:43,657
- Yes.
- That's why I like him.

1239
00:42:44,227 --> 00:42:45,656
The episode with him was fun.

1240
00:42:45,657 --> 00:42:47,027
I remember.

1241
00:42:47,927 --> 00:42:50,266
(The pre-grilled eels have finally arrived.)

1242
00:42:50,267 --> 00:42:51,436
Thank you.

1243
00:42:51,437 --> 00:42:52,837
- What a generous amount.
- Enjoy.

1244
00:42:53,637 --> 00:42:54,806
It's crispy on the outside, soft on the inside.

1245
00:42:54,807 --> 00:42:55,837
(Crispy outside and soft inside eels)

1246
00:42:56,637 --> 00:42:57,737
It looks good.

1247
00:42:57,837 --> 00:42:59,807
Eel helps you revitalize.

1248
00:43:00,337 --> 00:43:01,377
What a generous amount.

1249
00:43:03,747 --> 00:43:06,817
- Have the first piece, Jae Seok.
- Oh, gosh.

1250
00:43:08,417 --> 00:43:09,817
My goodness.

1251
00:43:10,087 --> 00:43:11,116
It's grilled to perfection.

1252
00:43:11,117 --> 00:43:12,357
As I expected...

1253
00:43:12,887 --> 00:43:14,686
(Dipping it in sauce)

1254
00:43:14,687 --> 00:43:16,787
I haven't had eel for lunch in a while.

1255
00:43:17,057 --> 00:43:18,827
- My gosh.
- Is it good?

1256
00:43:20,297 --> 00:43:22,426
(Hee Jun has it with perilla leaf.)

1257
00:43:22,427 --> 00:43:23,497
I love it.

1258
00:43:24,067 --> 00:43:25,667
(Amazed)

1259
00:43:25,837 --> 00:43:26,896
- Hold on. It looks good.
- It's...

1260
00:43:26,897 --> 00:43:27,936
Have the first piece, Jae Seok.

1261
00:43:27,937 --> 00:43:29,007
- With perilla leaf.
- Oh, gosh.

1262
00:43:30,007 --> 00:43:32,106
- It's crispy.
- Totally.

1263
00:43:32,107 --> 00:43:33,576
(A mouthful of ssam)

1264
00:43:33,577 --> 00:43:35,677
What a great place. I like this spontaneity.

1265
00:43:36,447 --> 00:43:37,646
(Navi Yoo eats, feeling relaxed.)

1266
00:43:37,647 --> 00:43:38,817
I love it.

1267
00:43:40,047 --> 00:43:41,247
It's crispy on the outside, soft on the inside.

1268
00:43:42,447 --> 00:43:44,147
Must-eat places are good too.

1269
00:43:44,617 --> 00:43:45,856
But I absolutely love it when the place...

1270
00:43:45,857 --> 00:43:46,957
you randomly choose is a must-eat place.

1271
00:43:47,157 --> 00:43:48,927
That's what I'm like on trips.

1272
00:43:49,227 --> 00:43:50,686
Planning out...

1273
00:43:50,687 --> 00:43:52,727
what to do and such...

1274
00:43:53,057 --> 00:43:55,597
gives me an idea of the trip I'll be going on,

1275
00:43:55,797 --> 00:43:57,766
making it boring.

1276
00:43:57,767 --> 00:43:58,767
I agree.

1277
00:43:59,137 --> 00:44:00,696
So, you're a total P.

1278
00:44:00,697 --> 00:44:02,607
Yes, I tried living in Jeju for a month,

1279
00:44:03,667 --> 00:44:05,177
and a week before we left, my wife started asking,

1280
00:44:05,807 --> 00:44:07,936
"When are we going there? What will we do then?"

1281
00:44:07,937 --> 00:44:09,577
"When do you want to take the ferry?"

1282
00:44:10,147 --> 00:44:11,476
- It's suffocating.
- I said, "Honey,"

1283
00:44:11,477 --> 00:44:14,177
"it's just a month. Can't we go without a plan?"

1284
00:44:14,577 --> 00:44:16,047
It must be frustrating for her, though.

1285
00:44:16,247 --> 00:44:19,116
- She must be a J.
- Totally.

1286
00:44:19,117 --> 00:44:21,017
- I can relate.
- It worries her.

1287
00:44:21,557 --> 00:44:23,227
I'm like Hee Jun.

1288
00:44:24,187 --> 00:44:25,956
It doesn't work, though. I just do what my wife wants.

1289
00:44:25,957 --> 00:44:26,957
- Exactly.
- Yes.

1290
00:44:27,057 --> 00:44:28,927
Otherwise, it's not living, but fighting there for a month.

1291
00:44:29,027 --> 00:44:30,096
That's true.

1292
00:44:30,097 --> 00:44:31,897
- It is.
- In conclusion,

1293
00:44:31,997 --> 00:44:33,997
you must listen to your wife.

1294
00:44:34,767 --> 00:44:36,367
- It was so funny.
- What?

1295
00:44:37,107 --> 00:44:38,407
When Kwon Sang Woo was here,

1296
00:44:38,677 --> 00:44:41,207
he said it was, "Anyway."

1297
00:44:41,877 --> 00:44:44,007
(What's the thing your wife says the most?)

1298
00:44:44,477 --> 00:44:46,546
(Anyway)

1299
00:44:46,547 --> 00:44:49,717
(It means, "I don't like it, so don't do it.")

1300
00:44:50,187 --> 00:44:54,156
(What Jae Seok's wife says the most)

1301
00:44:54,157 --> 00:44:56,486
(Did you hear me?)

1302
00:44:56,487 --> 00:44:58,996
(Something that a lot of married men could relate to)

1303
00:44:58,997 --> 00:45:00,197
"Are you listening to me?"

1304
00:45:00,827 --> 00:45:03,197
What does your wife say to you the most?

1305
00:45:03,297 --> 00:45:04,967
- To me?
- Yes.

1306
00:45:05,497 --> 00:45:07,197
"Hold on!"

1307
00:45:08,107 --> 00:45:09,936
(The chilling remark)

1308
00:45:09,937 --> 00:45:12,136
- It's the same as "anyway."
- Exactly.

1309
00:45:12,137 --> 00:45:15,106
They all imply similar meanings.

1310
00:45:15,107 --> 00:45:16,946
In his case, "hold on" means, "I've got a lot on my plate,"

1311
00:45:16,947 --> 00:45:18,877
- "so don't bother me."
- "Don't bother me."

1312
00:45:19,247 --> 00:45:21,017
"It's complicated enough, so don't pile on."

1313
00:45:22,087 --> 00:45:23,417
Does your wife have a favorite saying?

1314
00:45:24,987 --> 00:45:26,117
What she says to you the most often.

1315
00:45:26,557 --> 00:45:27,987
"I love you."

1316
00:45:28,327 --> 00:45:29,486
(Come on now.)

1317
00:45:29,487 --> 00:45:30,586
Seriously.

1318
00:45:30,587 --> 00:45:31,897
I also hear that every day!

1319
00:45:33,527 --> 00:45:34,657
Or something like this.

1320
00:45:34,827 --> 00:45:36,026
"I know, but..."

1321
00:45:36,027 --> 00:45:37,027
(It means, "I know, so you don't need to bring it up.")

1322
00:45:37,028 --> 00:45:38,697
- "I know, but..."
- "I know, but..."

1323
00:45:38,897 --> 00:45:40,136
- "I know."
- It sounds similar.

1324
00:45:40,137 --> 00:45:41,566
I also hear, "I love you,"

1325
00:45:41,567 --> 00:45:43,267
more than "Hold on."

1326
00:45:44,137 --> 00:45:46,706
- Suddenly, you're...
- You're trying to find a way out.

1327
00:45:46,707 --> 00:45:48,546
- Sorry.
- We're way past that.

1328
00:45:48,547 --> 00:45:49,576
(It's too late, kid.)

1329
00:45:49,577 --> 00:45:51,847
Maybe he must have been thinking about that.

1330
00:45:53,447 --> 00:45:54,717
We completely cleaned it.

1331
00:45:55,217 --> 00:45:57,446
(The grilled eel is gone.)

1332
00:45:57,447 --> 00:45:59,656
- It was delicious.
- It really was.

1333
00:45:59,657 --> 00:46:00,657
(They pleasantly got more stamina.)

1334
00:46:00,658 --> 00:46:02,756
It's going to be pretty expensive, though.

1335
00:46:02,757 --> 00:46:04,956
Look at all this food. I know it's expensive.

1336
00:46:04,957 --> 00:46:06,256
(The bill will be pretty high since it's eel.)

1337
00:46:06,257 --> 00:46:07,927
- The game...
- I should eat more.

1338
00:46:09,097 --> 00:46:10,667
- We should decide who pays.
- Yes.

1339
00:46:10,697 --> 00:46:12,736
- How about a game?
- Here's an idea.

1340
00:46:12,737 --> 00:46:14,907
(Deciding who pays)

1341
00:46:15,237 --> 00:46:17,006
We break a chili and count the seeds.

1342
00:46:17,007 --> 00:46:18,337
- The more seeds I have, the better?
- Yes.

1343
00:46:19,037 --> 00:46:20,676
The one with the fewest seeds loses.

1344
00:46:20,677 --> 00:46:22,847
- We pick a chili each.
- Sounds good.

1345
00:46:23,077 --> 00:46:24,976
- All right.
- Let go.

1346
00:46:24,977 --> 00:46:26,016
(They each pick a chili.)

1347
00:46:26,017 --> 00:46:27,147
Jeez.

1348
00:46:28,517 --> 00:46:29,517
It looks promising.

1349
00:46:29,518 --> 00:46:31,287
- I'll trust this guy.
- That guy?

1350
00:46:33,317 --> 00:46:34,517
What's the rule?

1351
00:46:34,887 --> 00:46:36,557
We break it...

1352
00:46:37,557 --> 00:46:38,557
and snap it once.

1353
00:46:38,558 --> 00:46:39,896
- Okay.
- And count the seeds?

1354
00:46:39,897 --> 00:46:40,996
- Yes.
- All right.

1355
00:46:40,997 --> 00:46:42,227
(Jae Seok goes first.)

1356
00:46:46,337 --> 00:46:47,467
One.

1357
00:46:47,797 --> 00:46:49,937
Just one snap.

1358
00:46:50,007 --> 00:46:51,406
- One snap.
- Don't turn it...

1359
00:46:51,407 --> 00:46:52,537
- or touch it hard.
- No rubbing.

1360
00:46:55,407 --> 00:46:57,206
(Still nothing)

1361
00:46:57,207 --> 00:46:58,846
- Nothing?
- One seed.

1362
00:46:58,847 --> 00:47:00,146
- One seed.
- I only got one?

1363
00:47:00,147 --> 00:47:01,786
- I thought there would be a lot.
- One.

1364
00:47:01,787 --> 00:47:03,346
- One seed.
- One seed.

1365
00:47:03,347 --> 00:47:04,416
Next.

1366
00:47:04,417 --> 00:47:05,956
It goes all over when you snap it too hard.

1367
00:47:05,957 --> 00:47:08,086
- Hee Jun.
- You need to aim well.

1368
00:47:08,087 --> 00:47:09,226
Today...

1369
00:47:09,227 --> 00:47:10,486
(Jae Seok: 1)

1370
00:47:10,487 --> 00:47:11,487
Oh, he's got two.

1371
00:47:12,327 --> 00:47:14,196
(He snaps it, but there's still two.)

1372
00:47:14,197 --> 00:47:15,566
- Nothing!
- Two.

1373
00:47:15,567 --> 00:47:17,526
- Hee Jun got two seeds.
- Two seeds.

1374
00:47:17,527 --> 00:47:18,637
- Okay.
- My turn, right?

1375
00:47:18,867 --> 00:47:20,036
They don't come out as much as I want.

1376
00:47:20,037 --> 00:47:21,037
(Jae Seok: 1, Hee Jun: 2)

1377
00:47:21,037 --> 00:47:22,037
(Happily eating it)

1378
00:47:22,038 --> 00:47:23,067
Here I go.

1379
00:47:24,107 --> 00:47:25,707
I'm feeling lucky today.

1380
00:47:26,137 --> 00:47:27,836
You have to break it the other way.

1381
00:47:27,837 --> 00:47:29,107
(Please...)

1382
00:47:32,277 --> 00:47:33,546
- He's got none.
- No seeds.

1383
00:47:33,547 --> 00:47:35,187
- Nothing.
- There aren't many seeds!

1384
00:47:35,987 --> 00:47:37,016
(Jae Seok: 1, Hee Jun: 2)

1385
00:47:37,017 --> 00:47:38,187
(Screaming)

1386
00:47:38,757 --> 00:47:40,256
(Smiling)

1387
00:47:40,257 --> 00:47:42,527
- What do I do with this guy?
- You got zero.

1388
00:47:42,557 --> 00:47:43,627
One good flick.

1389
00:47:43,887 --> 00:47:44,956
Nothing.

1390
00:47:44,957 --> 00:47:46,056
(Jae Seok: 1, Hee Jun: 2)

1391
00:47:46,057 --> 00:47:48,127
(Hae Soo: 0)

1392
00:47:48,697 --> 00:47:51,267
(A contrast of joy and despair because of one seed)

1393
00:47:51,427 --> 00:47:53,966
- One seed is still good.
- I won with one seed.

1394
00:47:53,967 --> 00:47:55,237
- What do I do?
- It's Hae Soo for now.

1395
00:47:55,437 --> 00:47:57,066
All right, Yeon Seok.

1396
00:47:57,067 --> 00:47:58,437
You win if you just get one.

1397
00:47:59,277 --> 00:48:01,236
- I have to do it hard.
- I had a feeling it was empty.

1398
00:48:01,237 --> 00:48:02,746
They're mostly at the top.

1399
00:48:02,747 --> 00:48:04,407
(Cautious)

1400
00:48:04,877 --> 00:48:05,977
Here I go.

1401
00:48:08,047 --> 00:48:10,417
(A bunch of seeds)

1402
00:48:10,887 --> 00:48:13,456
(Yeon Seok is 1st, and Hae Soo is last.)

1403
00:48:13,457 --> 00:48:14,857
- You're indeed...
- Why...

1404
00:48:15,027 --> 00:48:16,826
- Why does it hurt my pride?
- I have lots of seeds.

1405
00:48:16,827 --> 00:48:19,197
- Why is it so upsetting?
- I have lots of seeds!

1406
00:48:19,457 --> 00:48:21,027
- The seeds...
- This is...

1407
00:48:21,397 --> 00:48:22,796
- It's so strange, though.
- I have...

1408
00:48:22,797 --> 00:48:23,827
Why...

1409
00:48:24,527 --> 00:48:26,796
- This guy.
- Anyway, Hae Soo will pay!

1410
00:48:26,797 --> 00:48:28,936
- Yes.
- Thank you for the meal.

1411
00:48:28,937 --> 00:48:30,536
- You're welcome.
- Thanks, Hae Soo.

1412
00:48:30,537 --> 00:48:32,206
- Thank you, Hae Soo.
- I really enjoyed it.

1413
00:48:32,207 --> 00:48:34,107
I'll take the leftover chili.

1414
00:48:34,237 --> 00:48:35,246
It's very spicy.

1415
00:48:35,247 --> 00:48:37,446
Thank you. It was so delicious.

1416
00:48:37,447 --> 00:48:41,017
- Thank you.
- We highly praised it.

1417
00:48:41,377 --> 00:48:43,216
Thank you for the food.

1418
00:48:43,217 --> 00:48:44,816
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1419
00:48:44,817 --> 00:48:46,087
- Have a good day.
- Thank you.

1420
00:48:46,187 --> 00:48:47,656
- Thanks for the food.
- Thanks, Hae Soo.

1421
00:48:47,657 --> 00:48:48,786
Thank you.

1422
00:48:48,787 --> 00:48:50,627
No Seed Park Hae Soo.

1423
00:48:51,327 --> 00:48:52,657
- Seedless Hae Soo.
- Seedless Hae Soo.

1424
00:48:52,797 --> 00:48:54,396
(Happy)

1425
00:48:54,397 --> 00:48:55,696
Take the bus home.

1426
00:48:55,697 --> 00:48:56,896
(Seething)

1427
00:48:56,897 --> 00:48:58,437
I'm going to try it more at home.

1428
00:49:01,067 --> 00:49:02,666
- Sure.
- I'll come back.

1429
00:49:02,667 --> 00:49:03,766
That's good.

1430
00:49:03,767 --> 00:49:04,866
(Promising to get revenge)

1431
00:49:04,867 --> 00:49:06,576
- Now, there's no one lining up.
- Right.

1432
00:49:06,577 --> 00:49:07,577
(The waiting line is gone at the tofu place.)

1433
00:49:07,578 --> 00:49:09,606
- It's past lunchtime, so...
- Yes.

1434
00:49:09,607 --> 00:49:11,847
Hee Jun, it's like I'm staring at forsythias.

1435
00:49:12,577 --> 00:49:13,876
- It's spring.
- You're such a spring vibe.

1436
00:49:13,877 --> 00:49:15,716
(The four guys are excited about the scent of spring.)

1437
00:49:15,717 --> 00:49:18,116
What do you want to do the most when it's spring?

1438
00:49:18,117 --> 00:49:19,556
- When it's spring?
- Yes.

1439
00:49:19,557 --> 00:49:20,587
(What's the first thing he wants to do in the spring?)

1440
00:49:21,687 --> 00:49:23,827
I've never really thought about it.

1441
00:49:24,357 --> 00:49:26,457
I wish I could go watch some cherry blossoms.

1442
00:49:26,757 --> 00:49:28,227
- That's romantic.
- Yes.

1443
00:49:28,467 --> 00:49:30,096
I'd like to sit on some grass.

1444
00:49:30,097 --> 00:49:31,166
- Grass!
- Like at a park.

1445
00:49:31,167 --> 00:49:32,466
- Right.
- A park.

1446
00:49:32,467 --> 00:49:34,036
I want to watch nature.

1447
00:49:34,037 --> 00:49:35,507
- With a mat spread out.
- Yes.

1448
00:49:36,337 --> 00:49:37,867
Should we have a cup of coffee?

1449
00:49:38,037 --> 00:49:39,207
Yes, I'd like that.

1450
00:49:39,807 --> 00:49:42,546
Yes! I want coffee.

1451
00:49:42,547 --> 00:49:44,207
I'll look for a coffee shop.

1452
00:49:44,407 --> 00:49:45,746
I'll buy coffee.

1453
00:49:45,747 --> 00:49:46,776
(They spontaneously pick a coffee shop.)

1454
00:49:46,777 --> 00:49:47,877
Yeon Seok is...

1455
00:49:49,247 --> 00:49:50,617
They look like veterans.

1456
00:49:50,747 --> 00:49:52,816
- They seem experienced.
- Yes.

1457
00:49:52,817 --> 00:49:53,986
It's drip coffee.

1458
00:49:53,987 --> 00:49:55,887
Is this your signature item?

1459
00:49:56,127 --> 00:49:58,696
- We have a few signature drinks.
- Okay.

1460
00:49:58,697 --> 00:50:00,797
There's one with olive oil on top.

1461
00:50:01,397 --> 00:50:02,797
- Olive oil?
- Yes.

1462
00:50:02,867 --> 00:50:05,266
Would you like to try the one with olive oil?

1463
00:50:05,267 --> 00:50:06,996
- I'll give it a try.
- It's a signature drink.

1464
00:50:06,997 --> 00:50:07,997
(Olive oil coffee: 1)

1465
00:50:07,998 --> 00:50:10,107
I wonder what it tastes like.

1466
00:50:10,207 --> 00:50:12,037
- I'll have weak coffee.
- Weak coffee.

1467
00:50:12,377 --> 00:50:14,237
- I'll have coconut coffee.
- Okay.

1468
00:50:14,637 --> 00:50:16,776
- Yeon Shik is paying.
- Yes, coffee's on me.

1469
00:50:16,777 --> 00:50:19,017
- Thanks for the coffee.
- Thanks, Yeon Shik.

1470
00:50:19,277 --> 00:50:21,716
Yeon Seok used to make coffee during the "Narco-Saints" shoot.

1471
00:50:21,717 --> 00:50:23,186
- Right.
- He did?

1472
00:50:23,187 --> 00:50:24,287
Yes, Yeon Seok did.

1473
00:50:24,417 --> 00:50:26,786
- Was it in Jeju?
- Yes, Jeju.

1474
00:50:26,787 --> 00:50:30,227
I brought drip coffee bags to Jeju Island...

1475
00:50:30,457 --> 00:50:31,757
and made coffee.

1476
00:50:31,827 --> 00:50:35,926
And the other actors loved it when I made them coffee.

1477
00:50:35,927 --> 00:50:37,126
(Such as Hwang Jung Min and Ha Jung Woo)

1478
00:50:37,127 --> 00:50:38,936
Jung Min and Jung Woo both loved it.

1479
00:50:38,937 --> 00:50:41,136
If I remember correctly, you made them in the trunk.

1480
00:50:41,137 --> 00:50:42,536
He has a whole setup there.

1481
00:50:42,537 --> 00:50:45,007
(Their coffee is finally here.)

1482
00:50:46,507 --> 00:50:47,876
This must be the one with olive oil.

1483
00:50:47,877 --> 00:50:49,547
- I've never seen that before.
- Interesting.

1484
00:50:50,147 --> 00:50:52,176
There's olive oil on top,

1485
00:50:52,177 --> 00:50:54,646
so savor the scent of olive oil first.

1486
00:50:54,647 --> 00:50:55,717
Enjoy.

1487
00:50:56,047 --> 00:50:57,916
- There's olive oil on top.
- Lovely.

1488
00:50:57,917 --> 00:50:59,156
It's like a martini.

1489
00:50:59,157 --> 00:51:00,316
- How surprising.
- Let's clink glasses.

1490
00:51:00,317 --> 00:51:01,887
- Try it first.
- Thank you.

1491
00:51:02,487 --> 00:51:04,157
(Slurping)

1492
00:51:06,427 --> 00:51:07,627
Oh, it's good.

1493
00:51:09,697 --> 00:51:11,667
- It tastes so new.
- Mine is completely different.

1494
00:51:11,897 --> 00:51:13,137
- It's coconut coffee.
- How interesting.

1495
00:51:13,897 --> 00:51:15,206
- This is coffee?
- Olive oil...

1496
00:51:15,207 --> 00:51:16,636
There's coffee cream on top...

1497
00:51:16,637 --> 00:51:20,377
and coconut water beneath it.

1498
00:51:20,677 --> 00:51:22,476
I should try this at home.

1499
00:51:22,477 --> 00:51:23,976
(The four men elegantly enjoy coffee.)

1500
00:51:23,977 --> 00:51:25,246
The acidity...

1501
00:51:25,247 --> 00:51:28,117
I wish someone would make this kind of coffee in the morning.

1502
00:51:28,817 --> 00:51:30,146
- A neat cup of coffee.
- Weak coffee?

1503
00:51:30,147 --> 00:51:31,386
Your wife doesn't?

1504
00:51:31,387 --> 00:51:32,857
She needs to sleep.

1505
00:51:33,017 --> 00:51:35,127
- That's true.
- What are you saying?

1506
00:51:35,787 --> 00:51:38,896
Me too. She rarely does,

1507
00:51:38,897 --> 00:51:40,926
but she woke up early when I did for this shoot.

1508
00:51:40,927 --> 00:51:42,967
I said, "No, go back to bed."

1509
00:51:43,597 --> 00:51:44,626
That's basic etiquette.

1510
00:51:44,627 --> 00:51:46,297
I bring the hairdryer outside.

1511
00:51:48,037 --> 00:51:49,166
(The married men's game of perception)

1512
00:51:49,167 --> 00:51:52,407
- The hairdryer?
- They must rest well for us to...

1513
00:51:52,607 --> 00:51:54,877
- Yes.
- Then, where do you dry your hair?

1514
00:51:55,647 --> 00:51:58,006
- Just here and there.
- Here and there?

1515
00:51:58,007 --> 00:51:59,546
- Wherever there's an outlet.
- Where...

1516
00:51:59,547 --> 00:52:00,876
- Where she can't hear you.
- Exactly.

1517
00:52:00,877 --> 00:52:02,446
- Where she can't hear you.
- The farthest room...

1518
00:52:02,447 --> 00:52:03,886
- Wherever...
- from her bed.

1519
00:52:03,887 --> 00:52:06,117
they can sleep well.

1520
00:52:07,457 --> 00:52:09,626
Yeon Seok, you probably don't know since you're not married.

1521
00:52:09,627 --> 00:52:11,087
But when actors get married,

1522
00:52:11,787 --> 00:52:13,527
there's no place to read the scripts.

1523
00:52:14,127 --> 00:52:15,466
Where, then? In the bathroom?

1524
00:52:15,467 --> 00:52:16,527
We all have different places.

1525
00:52:16,567 --> 00:52:18,867
- Where do you read it?
- At my personal trainer's...

1526
00:52:19,137 --> 00:52:21,537
- That's ridiculous.
- office. I read it there.

1527
00:52:22,537 --> 00:52:24,366
I read it at my personal trainer's office.

1528
00:52:24,367 --> 00:52:26,307
What are you doing in someone else's place of business?

1529
00:52:26,337 --> 00:52:30,046
Strangely, I have the most free time when I'm there.

1530
00:52:30,047 --> 00:52:32,776
I have time to read the scripts after a workout.

1531
00:52:32,777 --> 00:52:33,917
Where do you read it?

1532
00:52:34,247 --> 00:52:35,616
I read it on a treadmill.

1533
00:52:35,617 --> 00:52:37,686
Come on, you're exaggerating.

1534
00:52:37,687 --> 00:52:39,156
- I'm serious.
- How...

1535
00:52:39,157 --> 00:52:40,157
On a tablet PC?

1536
00:52:40,158 --> 00:52:41,856
- Like a Galaxy Tab?
- I write it on a piece of paper...

1537
00:52:41,857 --> 00:52:43,287
and stick it on the treadmill.

1538
00:52:43,527 --> 00:52:45,126
- There's a place to stick it?
- Or...

1539
00:52:45,127 --> 00:52:47,796
- You know, it's a TV monitor, - Okay.

1540
00:52:47,797 --> 00:52:48,966
- but there are gaps.
- In the gaps.

1541
00:52:48,967 --> 00:52:50,667
A piece of paper goes through.

1542
00:52:50,867 --> 00:52:52,666
They have great coffee here.

1543
00:52:52,667 --> 00:52:53,697
Let's go.

1544
00:52:55,307 --> 00:52:57,606
- As long as we finish hard...
- Yes.

1545
00:52:57,607 --> 00:52:58,806
As long as we get them the prizes.

1546
00:52:58,807 --> 00:53:00,676
- Then, it'd be perfect.
- That'd be perfect.

1547
00:53:00,677 --> 00:53:03,047
I'd be able to go home with a smile on my face.

1548
00:53:03,807 --> 00:53:05,346
Should I get physical now?

1549
00:53:05,347 --> 00:53:09,016
Seong Nak Gu, Seong Ji Yu, and Seong Ji Won.

1550
00:53:09,017 --> 00:53:10,447
- They're a family.
- They are.

1551
00:53:10,517 --> 00:53:13,187
"With early training since the age of three,"

1552
00:53:13,487 --> 00:53:15,927
"our kids are already pros at pull-ups and bar hangs."

1553
00:53:16,157 --> 00:53:18,957
"Now, they can't live without a bar to swing on."

1554
00:53:19,227 --> 00:53:21,966
"Every day is a dopamine-fueled record-breaking war."

1555
00:53:21,967 --> 00:53:26,097
"Do you want to break a sweat with the Yaya family?"

1556
00:53:27,197 --> 00:53:29,806
- Pull-ups?
- I'm getting worried.

1557
00:53:29,807 --> 00:53:30,967
It's physical.

1558
00:53:32,377 --> 00:53:33,377
We're almost there.

1559
00:53:33,707 --> 00:53:35,877
- Are we?
- We turn there, and...

1560
00:53:36,307 --> 00:53:37,777
I think that's the one.

1561
00:53:38,007 --> 00:53:40,346
- The one that says, "CrossFit?"
- That's the one.

1562
00:53:40,347 --> 00:53:41,916
- It is a CrossFit gym.
- It really is.

1563
00:53:41,917 --> 00:53:43,017
- Right?
- It is.

1564
00:53:44,187 --> 00:53:46,016
This is it.

1565
00:53:46,017 --> 00:53:48,156
- Let's get changed.
- They work out.

1566
00:53:48,157 --> 00:53:49,157
(Half-excited and half-worried, they enter the CrossFit gym.)

1567
00:53:49,158 --> 00:53:50,827
The whole family must work out together.

1568
00:53:50,857 --> 00:53:51,996
They must.

1569
00:53:51,997 --> 00:53:53,427
(Shouting)

1570
00:53:53,597 --> 00:53:56,296
- I hear them.
- I hear them.

1571
00:53:56,297 --> 00:53:57,897
It's already loud.

1572
00:53:58,167 --> 00:53:59,836
I guess we'll actually break a sweat.

1573
00:53:59,837 --> 00:54:01,166
(What are they doing down here?)

1574
00:54:01,167 --> 00:54:02,937
- Oh, my gosh.
- What was that sound?

1575
00:54:04,467 --> 00:54:05,477
What...

1576
00:54:06,037 --> 00:54:07,836
- Hello there!
- Oh, dear.

1577
00:54:07,837 --> 00:54:09,207
- Oh, my.
- Hello.

1578
00:54:09,247 --> 00:54:10,706
- They're kids.
- He's not wearing a shirt.

1579
00:54:10,707 --> 00:54:11,747
That's cool.

1580
00:54:12,477 --> 00:54:13,946
Hello, everyone.

1581
00:54:13,947 --> 00:54:15,286
- Hello.
- Hello.

1582
00:54:15,287 --> 00:54:16,447
(Greeting them topless)

1583
00:54:16,887 --> 00:54:19,256
- Your body is...
- You're sweating so much!

1584
00:54:19,257 --> 00:54:21,057
- Are you Seong Nak Gu?
- Yes.

1585
00:54:21,457 --> 00:54:22,526
(Second Whenever Guests)

1586
00:54:22,527 --> 00:54:24,426
(Seong Nak Gu, Seong Ji Yu, and Seong Ji Won)

1587
00:54:24,427 --> 00:54:26,126
- Are they your son and daughter?
- Yes.

1588
00:54:26,127 --> 00:54:27,826
- Hi!
- I'm Ji Won.

1589
00:54:27,827 --> 00:54:29,526
- I'm Ji Yu.
- Ji Won and Ji Yu?

1590
00:54:29,527 --> 00:54:31,467
Ji Won and Ji Yu, nice to meet you.

1591
00:54:32,797 --> 00:54:34,267
- Hi.
- Hello.

1592
00:54:34,367 --> 00:54:37,536
- I thought they'd be siblings.
- Yes.

1593
00:54:37,537 --> 00:54:38,876
- We thought like that.
- Yes.

1594
00:54:38,877 --> 00:54:41,436
But it was the father and his children.

1595
00:54:41,437 --> 00:54:42,877
- That's right.
- That's cool.

1596
00:54:43,507 --> 00:54:45,077
- Let me get dressed.
- Yes, please.

1597
00:54:45,747 --> 00:54:47,817
It looks like you're already dressed.

1598
00:54:48,687 --> 00:54:49,716
(They're anxious without their dad.)

1599
00:54:49,717 --> 00:54:51,416
He looks so sturdy.

1600
00:54:51,417 --> 00:54:52,587
(Staring)

1601
00:54:52,887 --> 00:54:54,187
They're so nervous.

1602
00:54:55,657 --> 00:54:57,056
Adorable.

1603
00:54:57,057 --> 00:54:59,726
Ji Won and Ji Yu, do you also work out here?

1604
00:54:59,727 --> 00:55:00,757
- Yes.
- Yes.

1605
00:55:00,857 --> 00:55:03,126
- Were you doing this?
- It looks like it.

1606
00:55:03,127 --> 00:55:04,866
- Do you really know how?
- Yes.

1607
00:55:04,867 --> 00:55:06,097
(They were doing deadlifts with such cute faces.)

1608
00:55:07,197 --> 00:55:08,367
How old are you?

1609
00:55:08,437 --> 00:55:10,036
I'm 13,

1610
00:55:10,037 --> 00:55:11,306
- and he's 12.
- I'm 12.

1611
00:55:11,307 --> 00:55:12,977
You're 12 and 13.

1612
00:55:13,137 --> 00:55:15,106
And one of them becomes...

1613
00:55:15,107 --> 00:55:17,407
- an athlete in the future.
- An athlete.

1614
00:55:17,747 --> 00:55:18,977
This is early education.

1615
00:55:19,747 --> 00:55:21,016
- Nice to meet you.
- Hi.

1616
00:55:21,017 --> 00:55:22,446
- Hello.
- You're already sweating so much.

1617
00:55:22,447 --> 00:55:24,487
Yes, I was working out with my kids.

1618
00:55:25,247 --> 00:55:27,216
(Where they sweat together...)

1619
00:55:27,217 --> 00:55:29,187
(and test their limits)

1620
00:55:29,627 --> 00:55:33,357
(A place filled with shouts and cheers)

1621
00:55:34,397 --> 00:55:35,697
In 1, 2, 3.

1622
00:55:35,897 --> 00:55:38,027
(They have spare time from 3pm to 4pm.)

1623
00:55:38,897 --> 00:55:42,237
(The siblings come after school and exercise with their dad.)

1624
00:55:45,107 --> 00:55:47,877
(They bond through sweat.)

1625
00:55:47,937 --> 00:55:50,247
Ji Yu and Ji Won.

1626
00:55:50,677 --> 00:55:53,077
Nice to see you. How long have you been running it?

1627
00:55:53,647 --> 00:55:55,846
It's been seven years.

1628
00:55:55,847 --> 00:55:57,446
- That's a long time.
- That's long.

1629
00:55:57,447 --> 00:55:58,817
- Yes.
- But...

1630
00:55:59,557 --> 00:56:01,756
did you offer to work out together first?

1631
00:56:01,757 --> 00:56:05,287
No, I was working out at my CrossFit box,

1632
00:56:05,527 --> 00:56:06,897
and my kids sometimes visited.

1633
00:56:07,027 --> 00:56:08,356
- It was natural.
- They were...

1634
00:56:08,357 --> 00:56:10,697
around 2 or 3 when they did.

1635
00:56:10,967 --> 00:56:12,337
They used to hang on the bars.

1636
00:56:12,597 --> 00:56:14,397
They liked hanging when they were little.

1637
00:56:15,567 --> 00:56:16,866
I think it's been like two years exercising together.

1638
00:56:16,867 --> 00:56:18,366
- Two years.
- Yes.

1639
00:56:18,367 --> 00:56:19,877
And Ji Yu is a swimmer.

1640
00:56:20,137 --> 00:56:21,237
Oh, really?

1641
00:56:21,337 --> 00:56:22,507
That's incredible.

1642
00:56:22,607 --> 00:56:24,146
On our way in,

1643
00:56:24,147 --> 00:56:25,846
- we saw lots of shoes.
- Yes.

1644
00:56:25,847 --> 00:56:28,746
That could be an indicator of how many members you have.

1645
00:56:28,747 --> 00:56:30,587
That's true. But more were left behind.

1646
00:56:31,547 --> 00:56:33,556
They just leave the shoes behind when they quit?

1647
00:56:33,557 --> 00:56:34,557
Yes, most of them are left behind.

1648
00:56:34,558 --> 00:56:36,327
- They just ran off.
- Right.

1649
00:56:36,387 --> 00:56:38,796
They leave their shoes behind like, "Whatever."

1650
00:56:38,797 --> 00:56:41,327
Sometimes you wonder if you should go back for them.

1651
00:56:41,757 --> 00:56:43,026
- Right.
- Right.

1652
00:56:43,027 --> 00:56:44,726
- You want to get them in secret, - Yes.

1653
00:56:44,727 --> 00:56:46,336
but you'll have to run into the coach.

1654
00:56:46,337 --> 00:56:47,636
He's like, "Where were you? Are you back?"

1655
00:56:47,637 --> 00:56:49,937
- "I came back to work out."
- Yes.

1656
00:56:50,107 --> 00:56:51,536
That would make it awkward for both parties.

1657
00:56:51,537 --> 00:56:52,977
- Right.
- Yes.

1658
00:56:53,207 --> 00:56:55,137
That often happens.

1659
00:56:55,507 --> 00:56:57,606
Lots of people do CrossFit nowadays, right?

1660
00:56:57,607 --> 00:56:59,416
- Yes, more people do now.
- Right.

1661
00:56:59,417 --> 00:57:01,746
People prefer dopamine-fueled workouts.

1662
00:57:01,747 --> 00:57:03,246
- Yes, it's all about dopamine.
- Yes.

1663
00:57:03,247 --> 00:57:04,346
- Yes, it is.
- Yes.

1664
00:57:04,347 --> 00:57:07,587
When you feel like you're dead, the workout is over.

1665
00:57:08,487 --> 00:57:09,956
You look death in the eyes...

1666
00:57:09,957 --> 00:57:12,126
and have a rush of dopamine, then it's over.

1667
00:57:12,127 --> 00:57:14,697
She's smiling next to him, agreeing strongly.

1668
00:57:14,797 --> 00:57:16,567
(She got caught.)

1669
00:57:16,767 --> 00:57:19,696
Do you know what that feels like, Ji Yu?

1670
00:57:19,697 --> 00:57:22,907
Yes, I also had a near-death experience.

1671
00:57:23,707 --> 00:57:25,507
That smile told me everything.

1672
00:57:25,577 --> 00:57:27,876
- You had a near-death experience?
- She was strongly agreeing.

1673
00:57:27,877 --> 00:57:30,606
I can't tell how hard it was...

1674
00:57:30,607 --> 00:57:33,746
for Ji Yu to feel like it was a near-death experience.

1675
00:57:33,747 --> 00:57:35,047
First of all,

1676
00:57:35,747 --> 00:57:37,347
you taste blood.

1677
00:57:37,417 --> 00:57:38,586
Oh, my.

1678
00:57:38,587 --> 00:57:40,216
- She's tasted it.
- A sixth-grader...

1679
00:57:40,217 --> 00:57:41,956
- Exactly.
- said that.

1680
00:57:41,957 --> 00:57:43,656
Are there any specific characteristics...

1681
00:57:43,657 --> 00:57:45,356
for each age group among the members?

1682
00:57:45,357 --> 00:57:48,256
First off, most of them are introverts.

1683
00:57:48,257 --> 00:57:49,967
But the ones in their 20s turn into extroverts.

1684
00:57:50,127 --> 00:57:52,096
They become good friends.

1685
00:57:52,097 --> 00:57:53,796
- They cheer each other up.
- Yes.

1686
00:57:53,797 --> 00:57:55,466
- Because they cheer each other up.
- Yes.

1687
00:57:55,467 --> 00:57:56,536
That's how to get closer.

1688
00:57:56,537 --> 00:57:57,936
The ones in their 30s also become friends,

1689
00:57:57,937 --> 00:58:00,107
but those in their 40s are mostly angry.

1690
00:58:01,437 --> 00:58:03,107
- That's us.
- Yes.

1691
00:58:03,647 --> 00:58:05,207
As they work out,

1692
00:58:05,447 --> 00:58:06,716
they would swear.

1693
00:58:06,717 --> 00:58:08,616
Like Kim Dong Hyun. It's a lot of stress.

1694
00:58:08,617 --> 00:58:10,687
Those who are stressed out come for CrossFit.

1695
00:58:10,987 --> 00:58:14,857
Ji Won, what do you think makes CrossFit fun?

1696
00:58:15,757 --> 00:58:18,186
The thrill of supporting each other and finishing the workout?

1697
00:58:18,187 --> 00:58:19,826
- Supporting each other...
- Oh, my gosh.

1698
00:58:19,827 --> 00:58:22,027
How do you cheer each other up?

1699
00:58:22,497 --> 00:58:23,667
Let's go!

1700
00:58:24,367 --> 00:58:26,867
Like, "You can do it! One more!"

1701
00:58:27,067 --> 00:58:29,966
- I saw them clapping too.
- Yes.

1702
00:58:29,967 --> 00:58:32,637
Ji Won, you're not even taking off your grips.

1703
00:58:32,977 --> 00:58:35,707
Is there a workout you're good at?

1704
00:58:36,347 --> 00:58:37,347
Pull-ups.

1705
00:58:37,348 --> 00:58:38,846
- You're good at pull-ups?
- Pull-ups?

1706
00:58:38,847 --> 00:58:40,076
- Can you...
- Can we see it?

1707
00:58:40,077 --> 00:58:41,176
- Do you want to see it?
- Will you show us?

1708
00:58:41,177 --> 00:58:43,116
- Do you want to?
- Ji Won does pull-ups?

1709
00:58:43,117 --> 00:58:44,816
- Let's see his pull-ups.
- Yes.

1710
00:58:44,817 --> 00:58:47,016
- All right.
- That's admirable.

1711
00:58:47,017 --> 00:58:48,387
Can I feel your back?

1712
00:58:49,157 --> 00:58:50,857
- Your back.
- That's awesome.

1713
00:58:51,057 --> 00:58:52,327
(Amazed)

1714
00:58:53,327 --> 00:58:54,357
Shall we see it?

1715
00:58:55,057 --> 00:58:56,996
(Hanging with both hands)

1716
00:58:56,997 --> 00:58:58,227
His form is...

1717
00:58:59,167 --> 00:59:00,797
(Tiptoeing)

1718
00:59:01,437 --> 00:59:03,307
(He confidently does pull-ups.)

1719
00:59:04,637 --> 00:59:05,936
(The butterfly pull-up is a technique that uses...)

1720
00:59:05,937 --> 00:59:07,177
(body momentum to move in a circular motion.)

1721
00:59:08,307 --> 00:59:10,607
(Perfect butterfly pull-ups)

1722
00:59:11,347 --> 00:59:12,977
(Amazed)

